x 12px;font-size:12px;color:#94a3b8;\">GLP-1 pipeline dominance, strong balance sheet, premium justified by growth</td></tr>\n    <tr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;background:#2d0a0a;\"><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#fca5a5;\">AVGO</td><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;color:#f87171;\">62/100</td><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background:#fecaca;color:#b91c1c;border-radius:4px;padding:2px 8px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">HIGH</span></td><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#94a3b8;\">Stop broken + sector rotation pressure + 10% below entry; fundamentals intact but technical structure compromised</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#e2e8f0;\">TSM</td><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;color:#fbbf24;\">42/100</td><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background:#fef3c7;color:#d97706;border-radius:4px;padding:2px 8px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">MODERATE</span></td><td style=\"padding:9px 12px;font-size:12px;color:#94a3b8;\">Taiwan Strait geopolitical tail risk; otherwise clean fundamentals, strong foundry moat</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- DIVIDER -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:0 32px;\"><div style=\"border-top:1px solid #334155;\"></div></td></tr>\n\n<!-- WHAT TO DO TODAY -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:24px 32px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#94a3b8;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;margin-bottom:16px;\">What To Do Today</div>\n  <div style=\"background:#0f172a;border-radius:10px;padding:20px;\">\n    <table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#fca5a5;width:28px;vertical-align:top;\">1.</td><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;\"><b>Decide AVGO before Thursday open:</b> Option A (exit, -$15.65 net, free capital for VERA) or Option B (reset stop to $355, hold for $487 consensus). A non-decision removes structure from the trade &mdash; either path is better than limbo.</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#fbbf24;width:28px;vertical-align:top;\">2.</td><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;\"><b>Watch NVDA $203 (50-day MA):</b> If this breaks on volume, post-earnings consolidation becomes a breakdown. Current stop $199 &mdash; flag if price approaches on high volume.</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#fbbf24;width:28px;vertical-align:top;\">3.</td><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;\"><b>TSM follow-through:</b> June 10 drop 4.5% &mdash; watch if $393 is reclaimed in next 2&ndash;3 sessions. If not, sector rotation broadening.</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#4ade80;width:28px;vertical-align:top;\">4.</td><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;\"><b>LLY &mdash; hold and forget:</b> Riding toward TP2 $1,225. Next action only at TP2.</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#93c5fd;width:28px;vertical-align:top;\">5.</td><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;\"><b>VERA halal check (Musaffa):</b> Do this before IBKR approves. Need confirmation before entry &mdash; don't wait until the last minute before July 7 PDUFA.</td></tr>\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#94a3b8;width:28px;vertical-align:top;\">6.</td><td style=\"padding:6px 0;font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;\"><b>Hold $213.81 cash:</b> Do not deploy until AVGO decision made. Then VERA when IBKR clears and halal confirmed.</td></tr>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- DIVIDER -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:0 32px;\"><div style=\"border-top:1px solid #334155;\"></div></td></tr>\n\n<!-- EDUCATION -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:24px 32px;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#94a3b8;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;margin-bottom:16px;\">Today's Concept &mdash; #1 of 30</div>\n  <div style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#172554 0%,#1e293b 100%);border:1px solid #3b82f6;border-radius:10px;padding:24px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#93c5fd;margin-bottom:4px;\">Forward P/E vs Trailing P/E</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#475569;margin-bottom:16px;\">Concept 1/30 &middot; Valuation Series &middot; Applied today to NVDA post-earnings</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;margin-bottom:12px;line-height:1.7;\"><b style=\"color:#93c5fd;\">Trailing P/E</b> = Share price &divide; last 12 months actual EPS. Backward-looking &mdash; tells you what the market paid for earnings already in the bank.</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#e2e8f0;margin-bottom:12px;line-height:1.7;\"><b style=\"color:#93c5fd;\">Forward P/E</b> = Share price &divide; next 12 months consensus EPS estimate. This is what matters for growth stocks &mdash; you're paying for earnings that haven't happened yet.</div>\n    <div style=\"background:#0f172a;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;margin-bottom:14px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#fbbf24;margin-bottom:6px;\">Applied to NVDA right now:</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.7;\">NVDA trailing P/E: ~40x (last 12 months EPS). Looks expensive.<br>NVDA forward P/E: ~28x (next 12 months consensus estimates).<br>Analysts project EPS to roughly double in FY2027 as Blackwell ramp accelerates.<br><b style=\"color:#e2e8f0;\">The &ldquo;sell the news&rdquo; move after great earnings is often P/E compression back toward forward estimates.</b> Price drops not because the business is bad &mdash; but because the market had already priced in the beat. Forward P/E is the new anchor.</div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"background:#0f172a;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;margin-bottom:14px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#fbbf24;margin-bottom:6px;\">Why this is different from forex:</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.7;\">In FX you buy AUD/USD based on rate differentials or macro flows. In stocks, a large part of price movement is expectations about future earnings &mdash; P/E tells you how much the market is paying for those expectations. &ldquo;Cheap&rdquo; (low forward P/E) can mean growth is slowing. &ldquo;Expensive&rdquo; (high forward P/E like NVDA) can be fairly priced if earnings are growing fast enough.</div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"background:#0f172a;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#fbbf24;margin-bottom:6px;\">Rule of thumb:</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#e2e8f0;line-height:1.7;\"><b>Forward P/E &divide; EPS growth rate = PEG ratio</b><br>PEG &lt; 1.0 = potentially undervalued | PEG 1.0&ndash;2.0 = fair value | PEG &gt; 2.0 = priced for perfection<br><span style=\"color:#94a3b8;\">NVDA right now: ~28 fwd P/E &divide; ~100% EPS growth = PEG 0.28. By this measure, NVDA is cheap despite the headline number.</span></div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:14px;font-size:11px;color:#475569;font-style:italic;\">Next (#2): Revenue Growth vs Earnings Growth &mdash; why a company can beat on revenue and still miss on earnings, and why it matters for reading earnings reports.</div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;border-radius:0 0 12px 12px;padding:20px 32px;border-top:1px solid #1e293b;\">\n  <div style=\"font-size:11px;color:#334155;line-height:1.8;\">\n    <div>Prices as of June 11, 2026 close. Sources: Yahoo Finance, Google Finance.</div>\n    <div>Portfolio last updated: June 9, 2026. Next check: June 12, 2026 (Friday).</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px;color:#1e3a5f;font-style:italic;\">Personal research only &mdash; not financial advice. Halal verification via Musaffa (AAOIFI standards) required for all new positions.</div>\n  </div>\n</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n</td></tr>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>"
